'''''Soviet Storm: World War II in the East''''' ([[Russian language|Russian title]]: '''''Советский Шторм: Вторая мировая война на Востоке'''''; original Russian title — '''''Великая война''''', [[English language|English]]: ''The Great War'') is a 2011 17-episode [[Russia]]n television [[World War II]] series created by Anna Grazhdan, Artem Drabkin, and Aleksey Isaev.<ref>[http://starmediafilm.com/en/historical/velikaya_vojna "Soviet Storm: World War II in the East"]. Star Media. Retrieved 28 June 2014.</ref> An online version includes 18 episodes, ordered chronologically.

The series consists of 2 seasons, which document and recount the most important, bloody, costly, and decisive events, battles, and personalities on the [[Eastern Front (World War II)|Eastern Front]] in World War II.<ref>[http://www.history.co.uk/shows/soviet-storm-ww2-in-the-east "Soviet Storm: World War II in the East"]. History Channel. Retrieved 2014-04-25.</ref> Episodes generally last between 40 and 45 minutes and the overall series lasts approximately 12 hours.<ref name="Star Media"/>

== Series 1 ==
<onlyinclude>
{| class="wikitable" width="50%" style="margin-right: 0;"
! #
! Title
{{Episode list/sublist|Soviet Storm: World War II in the East
 |EpisodeNumber = 1
 |Title = Operation Barbarossa
 |ShortSummary = The [[Battle of Britain]] is over. The [[Luftwaffe]] has been driven to exhaustion, and [[Nazi Germany|Germany]] suffers its first major defeat. Even though [[United Kingdom|Britain]] remains undefeated, it is so isolated that [[Hitler]] has no concerns about turning his attention East. [[Operation Barbarrossa]], the German invasion of the [[USSR]], takes the Soviets completely by surprise and the [[Red Army]] suffers terrible casualties.<ref name="Star Media"/>
}}
{{Episode list/sublist|Soviet Storm: World War II in the East
 |EpisodeNumber = 2
 |Title = The Battle of Moscow
 |ShortSummary = October 1941, Germany's [[Army Group Center]] is only some 25 km west of [[Moscow]]. The [[Russian winter]], however, is only a few weeks away. With not enough soldiers or military equipment, the [[Stavka|Soviet high command]]'s only hope left is that the weather will save the capital. [[Battle of Moscow|The battle]] ends in a bloody failure for the [[German Army (Wehrmacht)|German Army]], and it is forced to retreat.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=11Bc1yZ6qsY "Soviet Storm: World War II in the East - The Battle of Moscow"]. Star Media's Official Youtube Channel. Retrieved 24 July 2014.</ref>
}}
{{Episode list/sublist|Soviet Storm: World War II in the East
 |EpisodeNumber = 3
 |Title = The Siege of Leningrad
 |ShortSummary = [[Leningrad]], a vital and large [[Baltic sea]] port, is facing the entire weight of [[Army Group North]]. The Soviets have no reserves to spare as the Battle of Moscow is about to begin. [[Wilhelm von Leeb]]'s Army Group North fails to take Leningrad, but begins [[Siege of Leningrad|a horrible siege that will last 872 days]], in which over a million civilians will die of starvation and disease.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LFx9fk4bbQ8 "Soviet Storm: World War II in the East - The Siege of Leningrad"]. Star Media's Official Youtube Channel. Retrieved 24 July 2014.</ref>
}}
{{Episode list/sublist|Soviet Storm: World War II in the East
 |EpisodeNumber = 4
 |Title = Stalingrad
 |ShortSummary = After the failure to take both Moscow and Leningrad, Hitler sets his sights on the oil fields in the [[Caucasus]]. If captured, the Red Army will lose 70%-90% of all its oil resources. Therefore, the famous city on the [[Volga]], [[Stalingrad]], must be "[[Order 227|held at all costs]]." The [[German General Staff]] thinks taking the city will be a matter of a few weeks, but events steadily turn against the Germans. It will be one of the most costly, famous, and decisive battles of the Second World War.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Gf8Rmf4m8rs "Soviet Storm: World War II in the East - Stalingrad"]. Star Media's Official Youtube Channel. Retrieved 24 July 2014.</ref> 
}}
{{Episode list/sublist|Soviet Storm: World War II in the East
 |EpisodeNumber = 5
 |Title = Operation Bagration
 |ShortSummary = By summer 1944, Germany has undeniably lost the battle of the USSR. After the Soviet victories at Moscow, Stalingrad, [[Kursk]], and Leningrad, the Soviet Union, with its practically unlimited resources of manpower and matériel, begins to rapidly push the Germans back toward the German border. On 22 June 1944, [[Stalin]] launches [[Operation Bagration]], named after a Russian hero of the [[Napoleonic Wars]]. Germany, by now, is running out of manpower, resources, and even faith in their charismatic Führer.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=i6UkVl3ZFuI "Soviet Storm: World War II in the East - Operation Bagration"]. Star Media's Official Youtube Channel. Retrieved 24 July 2014.</ref>
}}
{{Episode list/sublist|Soviet Storm: World War II in the East
 |EpisodeNumber = 6
 |Title = The Battle of Ukraine
 |ShortSummary = [[Kiev]], the Ukrainian capital, is, after a lengthy battle, back in Soviet hands. But now they have to clear the Germans and German allies out of the [[Crimea]] and liberate the rest of [[Western Ukraine]]. Hitler declared the Crimea a "[[German World War II strongholds|Festung]]," meaning it should be held at all cost and to the last man. The German [[17th Army (Wehrmacht)|17th Army]] was effectively destroyed in the process.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PbM4ITG0osM "Soviet Storm: World War II in the East - The Battle of Ukraine"]. Star Media's Official Youtube Channel. Retrieved 24 July 2014.</ref>
}}
{{Episode list/sublist|Soviet Storm: World War II in the East
 |EpisodeNumber = 7
 |Title = The Battle of Berlin
 |ShortSummary = Germany has without question lost [[World War II in Europe]], but Hitler, by now a [[Health of Adolf Hitler|heavily medicated and deluded character]], refuses to give up hope; he orders the roughly [[The Battle of Berlin|one million German soldiers left in the ruined city]] to defend [[Berlin]], now a strange mix of combat veterans, teenage boys from the [[Hitler Youth]], and old men from the [[Volkssturm|People's Army]]. Finally admitting all is lost, Hitler, [[Eva Braun|his girlfriend]], and [[Mass suicides in 1945 Nazi Germany|many of those present with him]] commit suicide to avoid captivity.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=U5JaM6ACoKM "Soviet Storm: World War II in the East - The Battle of Berlin"]. Star Media's Official Youtube Channel. Retrieved 24 July 2014.</ref>
}}
|}</onlyinclude>

== Series 2 ==
<onlyinclude>
{| class="wikitable" width="50%" style="margin-right: 0;"
! #
! Title
{{Episode list/sublist|Soviet Storm: World War II in the East
 |EpisodeNumber = 1
 |Title = The Battle of Kiev
 |ShortSummary = After the [[Battle of Smolensk (1941)|swift success at Smolensk]], Hitler has diverted the bulk of [[Heinz Guderian]]'s panzers down to the South, so as to capture the [[Ukraine|Ukrainian]] capital [[Kiev]], considered more important than Moscow in Hitler's mind. It begins a gigantic clash and turns out to be the [[First Battle of Kiev|biggest military encirclement in history]]. Despite heroic and long resistance, approximately six hundred and fifty thousand Soviet soldiers face captivity or death.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p2UqWRtBlBI "Soviet Storm: World War II in the East - The Battle of Kiev"]. Star Media's Official Youtube Channel. Retrieved 24 July 2014.</ref>
}}
{{Episode list/sublist|Soviet Storm: World War II in the East
 |EpisodeNumber = 2
 |Title = The Defence of Sevastopol
 |ShortSummary = [[Erich von Manstein]]'s soldiers have trapped a massive Soviet force in [[Crimea]], but the doomed troops have no intentions of surrendering, strongly motivated by patriotism. Manstein assembles the greatest concentration of artillery in history, which includes the world's biggest railway-gun nicknamed "[[Schwerer Gustav|Dora]]," and for eight months Soviets troops are savagely bombarded; destroying [[Sevastopol]]'s only harbor. Realizing [[Siege of Sevastopol (1941–42)|the battle]] is hopelessly lost, the Soviet forces finally surrender.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p_OuKwwzTvs "Soviet Storm: World War II in the East - The Defence of Sevastopol"]. Star Media's Official Youtube Channel. Retrieved 24 July 2014.</ref>
}}
{{Episode list/sublist|Soviet Storm: World War II in the East
 |EpisodeNumber = 3
 |Title = The Rzhev "Meat-Grinder
 |ShortSummary = The capture of [[Rzhev]], the city that connects all railroads in [[Western Russia]], is imperative. It will cost the lives of some 3 million Soviet soldiers and 500 000 German soldiers. It will take the Soviets a total of 3 years to throw the Germans firmly out of the city. These bloodbaths will become known by the [[veteran]]s and [[historian]]s as "[[Battles of Rzhev|The Rzhev Meat-Grinder]]".<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=h_UHNcqIYEg "Soviet Storm: World War II in the East - The Rzhev "Meat-Grinder"]. Star Media's Official Youtube Channel. Retrieved 24 July 2014.</ref>
}}
{{Episode list/sublist|Soviet Storm: World War II in the East
 |EpisodeNumber = 4
 |Title = The Battle of the Caucasus
 |ShortSummary = [[Paul Ludwig Ewald von Kleist|Ewald von Kleist]] has broken through to the [[Terek river]], slap in front of the vital oil fields of [[Grozny]] and [[Baku]]. Only freezing temperatures in the [[Caucasus]] prevent von Kleist's [[1st Panzer Army]] from breaking through to [[Caucasus|Ozoni Kizi]] and [[Tbilisi]]. The Soviets launch a desperate counter-attack that holds the Germans back. After the winter, Hitler makes a series of strategic blunders with von Kleist's forces, and he is forced to withdraw all his troops in the Caucasus to the [[Kuban]] bridge-head.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E_kU3qmL0MY "Soviet Storm: World War II in the East - The Battle of the Caucasus"]. Star Media's Official Youtube Channel. Retrieved 24 July 2014.</ref>
}}
{{Episode list/sublist|Soviet Storm: World War II in the East
 |EpisodeNumber = 5
 |Title = The War at Sea
 |ShortSummary = Hours before the start of [[Operation Barbarossa]], the Germans, along with their Finnish allies, begin mining the [[Gulf of Finland]] to prevent any naval evacuation of Soviet troops and ships. When Operation Barbarossa begins, [[Axis powers|Axis]] U-boats begin pounding the grand [[Soviet Navy]], primarily based at Leningrad. This turns out to be the start of a five year sea war against the Soviet Union's [[Baltic sea|Baltic]] Navy and the German and Finnish navies.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vbJESopFzug "Soviet Storm: World War II in the East - The War at Sea"]. Star Media's Official Youtube Channel. Retrieved 24 July 2014.</ref>
}}
{{Episode list/sublist|Soviet Storm: World War II in the East
 |EpisodeNumber = 6
 |Title = The Air War
 |ShortSummary = On 22 June 1941, [[Luftwaffe|German pilots]] were the first to see the sun rise. Before the day was over, the [[Soviet Air Forces]] had lost almost 2 000 aircraft. The early German air superiority gave a significant boost to German confidence, and severely damaged Soviet military capability and morale. The air wars over the [[USSR]] between the [[Soviet Union]] and [[Germany]] would be some of the biggest and toughest in military history.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EmgCaaSTJ9A "Soviet Storm: World War II in the East - The Air War"]. Star Media's Official Youtube Channel. Retrieved 24 July 2014.</ref>
}}
{{Episode list/sublist|Soviet Storm: World War II in the East
 |EpisodeNumber = 7
 |Title = The Partisan War
 |ShortSummary = By 1943-1944, as the Germans are desperately struggling to hold their ground, they are increasingly hindered by the [[Soviet partisans]], which contain many former [[Red Army]] soldiers that had been cut off behind enemy lines. The Germans responded with intensive counter-insurgency campaigns and brutal reprisals against the civilian population. The Germans will, because of this, fight a war against both the [[Soviet army]] and the Soviet population.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yb7rlsTgegY "Soviet Storm: World War II in the East - The Partisan War"]. Star Media's Official Youtube Channel. Retrieved 24 July 2014.</ref>
}}
{{Episode list/sublist|Soviet Storm: World War II in the East
 |EpisodeNumber = 8
 |Title = The Secret War
 |ShortSummary = Shortly before the outbreak of the [[Second World War]], the Polish and British have succeeded in de-coding the top secret German military codes known as "Enigma." This information, referred to as "Ultra" by the Allies, becomes vital for the Allies' military situation in [[North Africa]], the [[Soviet Union]], and [[Northern France]]. To the end of the war, the Germans were unaware that their top secret codes were being read, often in real-time, in [[London]].<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kKhR9gflK_8 "Soviet Storm: World War II in the East - The Secret War"]. Star Media's Official Youtube Channel. Retrieved 24 July 2014.</ref>
}}
{{Episode list/sublist|Soviet Storm: World War II in the East
 |EpisodeNumber = 9
 |Title = The Battle for Germany
 |ShortSummary = Germany is retreating on all fronts and suffering defeat after defeat. The breach of Germany's pre-War borders now seems inevitable. Desperate, Hitler orders all males between the ages of 16 and 70 to enlist and fight for the fatherland. [[Nazi ideologues]] put faith in victory and the [[Nazis]] seem to vanquish and suppress all forms of doubt and [[German resistance|resistance]] in the last months of the [[Nazi Germany|Reich]].<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fUFHAYCAD70 "Soviet Storm: World War II in the East - The Battle for Germany"]. Star Media's Official Youtube Channel. Retrieved 24 July 2014.</ref>
}}
{{Episode list/sublist|Soviet Storm: World War II in the East
 |EpisodeNumber = 10
 |Title = The War Against Japan
 |ShortSummary = The [[World War II in Europe|war in Europe]] is over. However, in the [[Pacific Ocean|Pacific East]], the United States is still fighting the Japanese, who consider surrender the greatest humiliation for a soldier. [[Stalin]] promises to help [[Franklin D. Roosevelt|Roosevelt]], but the dropping of the [[Atomic bomb]] on Japan suddenly alters the calculus for the Allies. Despite the devastation, the Japanese military vows to fight on. When reports of massive defeats in Manchuria at the hands of the Soviets reach the Japanese high-command, though, the military quickly capitulates. Even after the Japanese surrender, the Soviets use subtle diplomatic language to justify the continued capture of Japanese territory.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HjygZML_X-o "Soviet Storm: World War II in the East - The War Against Japan"]. Star Media's Official Youtube Channel. Retrieved 24 July 2014.</ref>
}}
|}</onlyinclude>

An online version adds an 18th episode, "The Battle of Kursk", and reorders the episodes more chronologically:

1.	Operation Barbarossa

2. 	The Battle of Kiev

3.	The Defence of Sevastopol

4. 	The Battle of Moscow

5.	The Siege of Leningrad

6.	Rzhev

7.	The Battle of Stalingrad

8.	The Battle for Caucasus

9.	The Battle of Kursk

10.	The Liberation of Ukraine

11.	Operation Bagration

12.	War in the Air

13.	War in the Sea

14.	The Partisan Movement

15.	Secret Intelligence of the Red Army

16.	The Battle for Germany

17.	Battle of Berlin

18. 	War Against Japan

